 Closer examination of its properties unfolds a rich array of perspectives like the status of barriers for extraction and government, the articulation of the topic focus structure, the fixation of wh-scope, the marking of clausal types, the interaction of syntactic structure with inflectional morphology as well as the determination of sentence mood and illocutionary force to mention just a few. The purpose of this book is to collect different and relevant studies in this field and to give a general overview of the various theoretical approaches concerned with morphological, syntactic and semantic properties together with the diachronic development of the left periphery.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aGenerative grammar. 0aGrammar, Comparative and generalxSyntax. 0aSemantics. 4aSyntax. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh1 aAxel, Katrin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBayer, Josef, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBrandner, Ellen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBredel, Ursula, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEden, Jan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFrey, Werner, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLohnstein, Horst, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLohnstein, Horst, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aLutz, Uli, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMeinunger, André, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aObenauer, Hans-Georg, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchwabe, Kerstin, econtributor.4ct